{# Page header #}
<div class="bg-ebcu-blue pt-24 pb-12">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white">How to read a beer label</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-white/90 max-w-2xl">
      Most labels are technically correct, but not always easy to interpret. Here's what to look for and why it matters.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Beer labels in the EU must include certain information by law, but the way it's presented can vary widely.
      Understanding what's required, what's optional, and what's marketing helps you make informed choices.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="my-8">
    <img src="/assets/images/man_label_2.jpg" alt="Reading a beer label" class="w-full rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2 italic">
      Taking time to read beer labels helps you understand what you're buying and make better choices.
    </p>
  </div>

  {# Topic Cards #}
